name: PrimaryHeadache
title: Primary Headache
description: This value set includes concepts for primary headache, i.e., headache that is not the result of another medical condition, such as migraine, tension, and cluster headaches.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This value set includes concepts for primary headache, i.e., headache that is not the result of another medical condition. Primary headache includes migraine headache, tension headache, and cluster headache.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this value set is to identify patients who have a diagnosis of primary headache. This element may map to "Diagnosis" Category of the Quality Data Model.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes all headaches that are not the result of another medical condition. Includes headache disorders with vascular, muscular, and unknown etiologies. Includes migraine headache, tension headache, and cluster headache, and cough headache.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes headache disorders triggered by immune system response (e.g., allergic, inflammatory). Excludes headaches with etiologies originating in the skeletal system (e.g., tooth or temporomandibular joint), peripheral nervous system (e.g., Tympanic plexus neuralgia syndrome). Excludes headaches secondary to medical procedure (e.g., post-lumbar puncture), head trauma (e.g., post concussion headache), and due to the effects of a drug. Excludes head pain syndromes occurring exclusively or primarily in specific sub-regions of the head (e.g., retinal migraine). Excludes headache associated with cerebrovascular events. Excludes non-disorder concept, i.e., SNOMED clinical finding concepts.)
